Gan , AGF rise on merger hopes . Shares in insurers Gan and AGF rose on Tuesday on merger speculation , particularly on talk of a possible takeover of Gan by AGF , market sources said . " It ' s the Axa / UAP phenomenon in the insurance sector which is making AGF move , " said a market operator . Gan was up four percent at 109 . 20 francs and Assurances Generales de France rose 4 . 17 percent to 187 . 50 at 1110 GMT . Speculation on various schemes has run in the market , including AGF buying the Athena unit from the Worms group , AGF buying Gan and AGF being bought by a foreign company , Allianz being the most often - cited name . 
